The user can start a new conversation about a daily need from the IGOOR homepage.

**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

Needs are organized across two pages: the first should include the most frequent needs. You can move from one page to another by clicking the arrow:

For example, clicking on the large "heating" button gives us sentence predictions across three columns:

**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

On the left, we have sentences to INCREASE the heating temperature; on the right (visually opposite) to DECREASE it. In the middle, other suggestions that may be more neutral or go beyond this opposition.

ALL suggestions are personalized based on the context and generated in real-time. These are therefore not buttons with pre-written sentences, as found in other software (e.g., Grid3).

## Customize Daily Needs

**After installing IGOOR, the needs are drawn from a list created using patient lists. It is important to personalize your list very quickly and to update it regularly.**
